Description: Body sherd of Attic, almost certainly black-figured, pottery open vessel, possibly a krater; concave profile; interior glazed streaky black; exterior: on neck, maeander pattern; below, possible figure with added red and inscription.
Bibliographic references: Vase / Catalogue of Vases in the British Museum (B601.21)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0229) (Phase 1)
